ope by passenger traffic]]\n*[[List of the largest airports in the Nordic countries]]<sup>1</sup>\n*[[List of the busiest airports in the Baltic states]]<sup>1</sup>\n \n<sup>1</sup> <small>Includes very detailed statistics regarding busiest passenger air routes to/from and within this region</small>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Aviation statistics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:World's Busiest Passenger Air Routes}}\n[[Category:Aviation statistics]]\n[[Category:Aviation-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of superlatives|Busiest Passenger Air Routes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThese are lists of the busiest air routes by the number of passengers flown, by seat capacity and by aircraft movements.\n\n==By number of passengers==\n\n===World===\n'''The top 100 busiest air routes'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:85%\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Airport 1\n!Airport 2\n!Distance (km)\n!2018<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/29/breaking-news/286313/busiest-routes-in-the-world-the-top-100/|title=Busiest routes in the world - the top 100|website=Routesonline|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref>\n!2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/29/breaking-news/280568/these-are-the-top-100-busiest-routes-on-earth/|title=These are the top 50 busiest routes on earth|date=September 2018|publisher=RoutesOnline}}</ref>\n!Type\n|-\n|align=center|1 || {{flagdeco|ROK}} [[Jeju International Airport|Jeju]] ||{{flagdeco|ROK}} [[Gimpo International Airport|Seoul-Gimpo]]\n|align=center|449\n|14,107,414\n|align=center|13,460,306\n|align=center|Domestic\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |2 ||{{flagdeco|JPN}} [[New Chitose Airport|Sapporo]]||{{flagdeco|JPN}} [[Haneda Airport|Tokyo-Haneda]]\n| align=\"center\" |835\n|9,698,639\n| align=\"center\" |8,726,502\n| align=\"center\" |Domestic\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |3 ||{{flagdeco|AUS}} [[Sydney Airport|Sydney]]||{{flagdeco|AUS}} [[Melbourne Airport|Melbourne]]\n| align=\